Introduction¶

There is no doubt that Film industry is one of the most idustries that have high revenues, the concept of paying millions of money on choosing the best crew, cast, locations and also sophisticated equipments to bring out a high quality movies which make much more revenue than what is paid, this is what makes good films companies are more wanted than others

for this dataset which collected from TMDB we have some information about more than 10,000 movies like cast, budget, revenue and more so we will ask some question to know what are the factors of a good movie

Q1. Which genres that people are most like?¶

as some features have alot of values stored in each row, we will define a function that extract and generate countplots for the each value

In [16]:
#this function can be applied for every feature that have more then 1 value separated with this sign '|'
def extract_info(df,feature,list_name,dict_name,head_number):
    var = df[feature].str.split("|")

    for i in var:
        for j in i:
            list_name.append(j)
            
    list_name = pd.Series(list_name)
    list_name = list_name.drop_duplicates()
    
    for i in list_name:
        dict_name[i] = df[df[feature].str.contains(i)].shape[0]
        new_df = pd.DataFrame(list(dict_name.items()),columns = [feature,'Count'])
        new_df = new_df.sort_values(by = "Count", ascending=False)
        
        
    return sns.barplot(new_df[feature].head(head_number),new_df['Count'].head(head_number)).set_title(feature+" counts", fontsize=18),plt.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=70),new_df.head()

Conclusions¶

so now we can have some clear answers about question that mentioned previously

Q1. Which genres that directors are focus on the most?¶

so these 4 genres are more chosen by directors to focus on in their movies : Drama, Comedy, Thriller and Action

Q2. which are the companies contributes in more movies than others?¶

by far, Universal Pictures have the highest number of contributing in movies production because universal and Universal Pictures are the same company, then comes Warner Bros, Columbia Pictures and paramount Pictures

Q3. who is the best director?¶

as we said before, there is no clear answer for this question, so we tried to answer it according to some factors like Budget & Revenue, runtime, vote count and vote Average so,

for Budget & Revenue we have Steven Spielberg ,

for runtime we have also Steven Spielberg

for vote count we have Christopher Nolan and in second place Steven Spielberg

and finally for vote Average we have Damien Chazelle

so as overall we can say that Steven Spielberg is the most common name in these features

Q4. what affects revenue?¶

as we have numerical and categorical features, we need to deal with them separatly, so

for numerical features we applied pearson's correlation to see which features are more related to revenue and they are popularity, budget, vote_count, budget_adj and revenue_adj

also, we saw the changes happened to revenue and budget according to changes of release year and we found that revenue is increasing over years, unlike budget which seems to be decreasing

for categorical features it's hard to apply ordinary correlation checks because each feature have more than two levels, means that each feature have alot of values in it so we will leave them for now

the limitaions i have faced in this project¶

1 - as i mentioned in Q4, it's hard to represent the correlation between discrete variable and categorical variables that have large number of values, for example if had a variable called gender, then it will have two classes: male and female, but for variable like cast we have a lot of actors and actress's names that represent large number of classes

after some research i found that there are some statistics techniques, mention in this questions on qoura, and found this picture as a good compilation of these techniques but the implementaion for some of them is beyond my experience and some others i used only in machine learning and don't know how exactly use them in this case

2 - some features had more than one value or string in one row, for example, genres feature have this value in first row Action|Adventure|Science Fiction|Thriller, separating this feature could end with representing some misleading plots

3 - in feature like production_companies some values has different names but actully they are the thing, for example universal and Universal Pictures each one of them were second and third in the plot respectivily put actully they are the same company and by combining them together they become in the first place, so for me there wasn't a clear way to fix this issue
